no.motif

Class Iterate

  • java.lang.Object
    • no.motif.Iterate

  • public final class Iterate
extends Object
    Operations for containers, e.g. arrays, lists, sets, or any implementation of Iterable. Can also treat Strings as a container of Characters.

      • byOrderingOf

        public static <T extends Comparable<T>> EnhancedComparator<T> byOrderingOf(Class<T> comparableType)
        Convert a type with natural ordering, i.e. implements Comparable, to an external Comparator. This is a little quirk to provide a typesafe way to sort iterables containing Comparables, instead of risking a runtime ClassCastException. Pass this to the .sorted(..) method to get elements as a sorted list.
        Parameters:
        comparableType - The Comparable type to create a Comparator from.
        Returns:
        the Comparator

      • last

        public static <T> Fn<T,T> last(Fn<? super T,? extends T> next)
        Using a function which takes an object and returns another object of the same type, recursively call this function until it yields null, and ultimately yield the last object.
        Parameters:
        next - The function which takes an object and yields another object of the same type. This is typically used for objects implementing a linked list-like structure, where each object refers to the next in a chain.
        Returns:
        A function which will descend the chain and yield the last object. If the given next Fn never returns null, calling this returned function will result in an infinite recursion.

      • toIterable

        public static <I,O> Fn<I,Iterable<O>> toIterable(Fn<I,O[]> yieldsArray)
        A bridge from functions yielding arrays, to functions yielding iterables.
        Parameters:
        yieldsArray - the array-yielding function.
        Returns:
        an adapted function yielding an iterable of the array yielded from the original function.
